<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-11-08T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-11-08T10:00:00-05:00" n="478" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.01/3: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-08T10:00:00-05:00">November 8, 1930—10
                                a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>82. Your November 5, 11 a.m. You will today, but not earlier than 2 hours
                            from this time, answer the note of November 3d from the Brazilian
                            Government by stating “that this Government will be happy to continue
                            with the new Government the same friendly relations as with its
                            predecessors.”</p>
                        <p>You will at once confidentially advise your British, Colombian and Cuban
                            colleagues what your instructions are.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>